{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871571409,"sessionID":"ses_285cee01cffe6FVMs7Bj8Kv4Ql","part":{"id":"prt_d7a31b15f001WfvPC7DcO4dYLa","messageID":"msg_d7a31a20f001iWWAK8y2UvsERd","sessionID":"ses_285cee01cffe6FVMs7Bj8Kv4Ql","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e62d4468a91e47b78c50fc75","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements the `MetadataService` and associated data models for the AgentCube CLI toolkit (`cmd/cli`). The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Centralize metadata management** - Provide a single source of truth for agent configuration across the CLI\n8: 2. **Enable workspace validation** - Validate agent workspace structure and language-specific requirements\n9: 3. **Support metadata lifecycle** - Load, save, update, and validate agent metadata throughout the agent lifecycle\n10: 4. **Ensure schema correctness** - Use Pydantic validation to enforce metadata schema constraints\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n15: **Language:** Python  \n16: **Size:** M\n17: \n18: This AR covers:\n19: \n20: - **In scope:**\n21:   - `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with all required fields and validators\n22:   - `MetadataService` class with load/save/update/validate operations\n23:   - `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI option mapping\n24:   - Workspace validation for Python and Java agents\n25:   - YAML persistence with fallback file naming\n26:   - Integration with `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`\n27: \n28: - **Out of scope:**\n29:   - CLI command implementations (separate ARs)\n30:   - Docker/Kubernetes service integrations\n31:   - AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter CRD operations\n32: \n33: ## Current State Analysis\n34: \n35: ### Existing Implementation\n36: \n37: Per the design specification (`cli-toolkit/design.md`), the following components exist:\n38: \n39: 1. **Package Layout:**\n40:    - `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` - `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService`\n41:    - `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` - `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n42:    - `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` - Uses `MetadataService` internally\n43: \n44: 2. **AgentMetadata Fields:**\n45:    - Core: `agent_name`, `description`, `language`, `entrypoint`, `port`, `build_mode`, `version`\n46:    - Image: `image`, `auth`, `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password`\n47:    - Deployment: `region`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`\n48:    - Probes: `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`\n49:    - Runtime: `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`\n50: \n51: 3. **Validators:**\n52:    - `validate_language` - Restricts to `['python', 'java']`\n53:    - `validate_build_mode` - Restricts to `['local', 'cloud']`\n54:    - `validate_port` - Range `1..65535`\n55: \n56: 4. **MetadataService Methods:**\n57:    - `load_metadata(workspace_path)` - Load from YAML with fallbacks\n58:    - `save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` - Persist to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n59:    - `update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` - Partial update helper\n60:    - `validate_workspace(workspace_path)` - Structure validation\n61:    - `_validate_python_workspace(...)` - Python-specific checks\n62:    - `_validate_java_workspace(...)` - Java-specific checks\n63: \n64: ### Issues Identified\n65: \n66: 1. **Documentation drift** - Some docs reference `agentcube.yaml` instead of canonical `agent_metadata.yaml`\n67: 2. **Discoverability** - `StatusRuntime` not exported in `__all__` despite being part of runtime suite\n68: 3. **Incomplete error handling** - `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but unused in SDK\n69: \n70: ## Proposed Changes\n71: \n72: ### 1. AgentMetadata Model\n73: \n74: Define comprehensive Pydantic model in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`:\n75: \n76: ```python\n77: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n78:     \"\"\"Agent metadata schema with validation.\"\"\"\n79:     \n80:     # Core identification\n81:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n82:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n83:     \n84:     # Language and execution\n85:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n86:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n87:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n88:     \n89:     # Build configuration\n90:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n91:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n92:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n93:     \n94:     # Dependency management\n95:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n96:     \n97:     # Image registry\n98:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n99:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n100:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n101:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n102:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n103:     \n104:     # Runtime endpoints\n105:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n106:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n107:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n108:     \n109:     # Health probes\n110:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n111:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n112:     \n113:     # Runtime state\n114:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n115:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n116:     \n117:     # Deployment info\n118:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n119:     \n120:     # Validators\n121:     @field_validator(\"language\")\n122:     @classmethod\n123:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n124:         v = v.lower()\n125:         if v not in [\"python\", \"java\"]:\n126:             raise ValueError(\"language must be 'python' or 'java'\")\n127:         return v\n128:     \n129:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n130:     @classmethod\n131:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n132:         v = v.lower()\n133:         if v not in [\"local\", \"cloud\"]:\n134:             raise ValueError(\"build_mode must be 'local' or 'cloud'\")\n135:         return v\n136:     \n137:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n138:     @classmethod\n139:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n140:         if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n141:             raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n142:         return v\n143: ```\n144: \n145: ### 2. MetadataService Implementation\n146: \n147: Implement service class in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`:\n148: \n149: ```python\n150: class MetadataService:\n151:     \"\"\"Service for agent metadata management.\"\"\"\n152:     \n153:     METADATA_FILES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n154:     \n155:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n156:         self.verbose = verbose\n157:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n158:     \n159:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n160:         \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace, trying fallback filenames.\"\"\"\n161:         for filename in self.METADATA_FILES:\n162:             metadata_file = workspace_path / filename\n163:             if metadata_file.exists():\n164:                 try:\n165:                     content = metadata_file.read_text()\n166:                     data = yaml.safe_load(content)\n167:                     return AgentMetadata(**data)\n168:                 except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n169:                     raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML in {filename}: {e}\")\n170:                 except ValidationError as e:\n171:                     raise ValueError(f\"Invalid metadata schema: {e}\")\n172:         \n173:         # No metadata file found - return defaults\n174:         return AgentMetadata(\n175:             agent_name=workspace_path.name,\n176:             entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n177:         )\n178:     \n179:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n180:         \"\"\"Save metadata to canonical filename.\"\"\"\n181:         metadata_file = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n182:         data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n183:         content = yaml.dump(\n184:             data,\n185:             default_flow_style=False,\n186:             indent=2,\n187:             sort_keys=False,\n188:         )\n189:         metadata_file.write_text(content)\n190:     \n191:     def update_metadata(\n192:         self,\n193:         workspace_path: Path,\n194:         updates: Dict[str, Any],\n195:     ) -> AgentMetadata:\n196:         \"\"\"Load, update, save, and return metadata.\"\"\"\n197:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n198:         updated = metadata.model_copy(update=updates)\n199:         self.save_metadata(workspace_path, updated)\n200:         return updated\n201:     \n202:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n203:         \"\"\"Validate workspace structure and content.\"\"\"\n204:         if not workspace_path.exists():\n205:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n206:         \n207:         if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n208:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n209:         \n210:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n211:         \n212:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n213:             self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n214:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n215:             self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n216:         \n217:         return True\n218:     \n219:     def _validate_python_workspace(\n220:         self,\n221:         workspace_path: Path,\n222:         metadata: AgentMetadata,\n223:     ) -> None:\n224:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n225:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n226:         if not py_files:\n227:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n228:     \n229:     def _validate_java_workspace(\n230:         self,\n231:         workspace_path: Path,\n232:         metadata: AgentMetadata,\n233:     ) -> None:\n234:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n235:         pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n236:         if not pom_xml.exists():\n237:             raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")\n238: ```\n239: \n240: ### 3. MetadataOptions Dataclass\n241: \n242: Define options class in `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`:\n243: \n244: ```python\n245: from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n246: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n247: \n248: \n249: @dataclass\n250: class MetadataOptions:\n251:     \"\"\"CLI options mapped to metadata fields.\"\"\"\n252:     \n253:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n254:     language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n255:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n256:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n257:     build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n258:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n259:     description: Optional[str] = None\n260:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n261:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n262:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n263:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n264:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n265:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n266:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n267:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n268:     \n269:     @classmethod\n270:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n271:         \"\"\"Create from CLI options dict.\"\"\"\n272:         return cls(\n273:             agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\"),\n274:             language=options.get(\"language\", \"python\"),\n275:             entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\"),\n276:             port=options.get(\"port\", 8080),\n277:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n278:             requirements_file=options.get(\"requirements_file\"),\n279:             description=options.get(\"description\"),\n280:             workload_manager_url=options.get(\"workload_manager_url\", \"\"),\n281:             router_url=options.get(\"router_url\", \"\"),\n282:             readiness_probe_path=options.get(\"readiness_probe_path\", \"\"),\n283:             readiness_probe_port=options.get(\"readiness_probe_port\", 8080),\n284:             registry_url=options.get(\"registry_url\", \"\"),\n285:             registry_username=options.get(\"registry_username\", \"\"),\n286:             registry_password=options.get(\"registry_password\", \"\"),\n287:             agent_endpoint=options.get(\"agent_endpoint\", \"\"),\n288:         )\n289: ```\n290: \n291: ### 4. Integration with PackRuntime\n292: \n293: Update `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` to use `MetadataService`:\n294: \n295: ```python\n296: class PackRuntime:\n297:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n298:         self.verbose = verbose\n299:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n300:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n301:     \n302:     def pack(\n303:         self,\n304:         workspace_path: Path,\n305:         **options: Any,\n306:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n307:         \"\"\"Package agent workspace.\"\"\"\n308:         # Validate workspace structure\n309:         self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n310:         \n311:         # Load or create metadata\n312:         metadata_options = MetadataOptions.from_options(options)\n313:         metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, metadata_options)\n314:         \n315:         # Apply CLI overrides\n316:         metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, metadata_options)\n317:         \n318:         # Validate language compatibility\n319:         self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n320:         \n321:         # Process dependencies\n322:         self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n323:         \n324:         # Generate Dockerfile\n325:         dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n326:         \n327:         # Update metadata with packaging info\n328:         self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n329:         \n330:         # Prepare output\n331:         final_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n332:         \n333:         return {\n334:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n335:             \"workspace_path\": str(final_path),\n336:             \"metadata_path\": str(final_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n337:             \"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None,\n338:         }\n339:     \n340:     def _load_or_create_metadata(\n341:         self,\n342:         workspace_path: Path,\n343:         options: MetadataOptions,\n344:     ) -> AgentMetadata:\n345:         \"\"\"Load existing metadata or create new.\"\"\"\n346:         try:\n347:             metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n348:         except (FileNotFoundError, ValueError):\n349:             # Create new metadata with defaults\n350:             metadata = AgentMetadata(\n351:                 agent_name=options.agent_name or workspace_path.name,\n352:                 language=options.language or \"python\",\n353:                 entrypoint=options.entrypoint or \"python main.py\",\n354:                 port=options.port or 8080,\n355:                 build_mode=options.build_mode or \"local\",\n356:             )\n357:         return metadata\n358: ```\n359: \n360: ### 5. Module Exports\n361: \n362: Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to include `StatusRuntime`:\n363: \n364: ```python\n365: __version__ = \"0.1.0\"\n366: __author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"\n367: __email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"\n368: \n369: from agentcube.cli.main import app\n370: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n371: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n372: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n373: from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n374: from agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime\n375: \n376: __all__ = [\n377:     \"app\",\n378:     \"PackRuntime\",\n379:     \"BuildRuntime\",\n380:     \"PublishRuntime\",\n381:     \"InvokeRuntime\",\n382:     \"StatusRuntime\",  # Added for consistency\n383: ]\n384: ```\n385: \n386: ## Impact Analysis\n387: \n388: ### Files to Create\n389: \n390: | File | Purpose |\n391: |------|---------|\n392: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n393: \n394: ### Files to Modify\n395: \n396: | File | Changes | Impact |\n397: |------|---------|--------|\n398: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Implement `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` | High - core functionality |\n399: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Integrate `MetadataService` | Medium - uses service |\n400: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Export `StatusRuntime` | Low - additive |\n401: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-export `MetadataOptions` | Low - convenience |\n402: \n403: ### Dependencies\n404: \n405: From `pyproject.toml`:\n406: \n407: ```toml\n408: dependencies = [\n409:     \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n410:     \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",      # For AgentMetadata\n411:     \"pyyaml>=6.0\",          # For YAML persistence\n412:     \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n413:     \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n414:     \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n415:     \"packaging>=23.0\",\n416:     \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n417:     \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n418: ]\n419: \n420: [project.optional-dependencies]\n421: k8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\n422: dev = [\n423:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n424:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n425:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n426:     \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n427:     \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n428:     \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n429:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n430: ]\n431: test = [\n432:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n433:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n434:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n435:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n436:     \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n437: ]\n438: ```\n439: \n440: ### Backward Compatibility\n441: \n442: - **Metadata file naming**: Canonical `agent_metadata.yaml` with fallbacks to `agent.yaml` and `metadata.yaml`\n443: - **Schema evolution**: Pydantic `Optional` fields allow gradual adoption\n444: - **Default values**: Sensible defaults minimize required configuration\n445: \n446: ### Testing Impact\n447: \n448: Unit tests required for:\n449: \n450: - `AgentMetadata` validation (language, build_mode, port)\n451: - `MetadataService.load_metadata()` with all fallback files\n452: - `MetadataService.save_metadata()` YAML format\n453: - `MetadataService.validate_workspace()` for Python and Java\n454: - `MetadataOptions.from_options()` mapping\n455: \n456: ## Alternatives Considered\n457: \n458: ### Alternative 1: JSON Metadata\n459: \n460: Use JSON instead of YAML for metadata persistence.\n461: \n462: **Pros:**\n463: - Native Python support (no extra dependency)\n464: - Faster parsing\n465: - Strict syntax\n466: \n467: **Cons:**\n468: - Less human-readable\n469: - No comments support\n470: - Inconsistent with Kubernetes manifests\n471: \n472: **Decision:** YAML is preferred for consistency with Kubernetes ecosystem.\n473: \n474: ### Alternative 2: Configuration Dataclass\n475: \n476: Use a simple dataclass instead of Pydantic model.\n477: \n478: **Pros:**\n479: - No external dependency\n480: - Simpler implementation\n481: - Faster instantiation\n482: \n483: **Cons:**\n484: - No built-in validation\n485: - Manual type checking\n486: - No serialization helpers\n487: \n488: **Decision:** Pydantic provides essential validation and serialization.\n489: \n490: ### Alternative 3: Environment Variables Only\n491: \n492: Store configuration in environment variables instead of files.\n493: \n494: **Pros:**\n495: - No file management\n496: - Easy for containers\n497: - Secret-friendly\n498: \n499: **Cons:**\n500: - No persistence\n501: - Hard to version\n502: - Poor discoverability\n503: \n504: **Decision:** File-based metadata with optional env overrides.\n505: \n506: ### Alternative 4: Central Configuration Class\n507: \n508: Create a `Configuration` class like the Python SDK pattern.\n509: \n510: **Pros:**\n511: - Single source of truth\n512: - Easier to audit defaults\n513: - Consistent interface\n514: \n515: **Cons:**\n516: - More boilerplate\n517: - Less flexible per-component\n518: - Overkill for CLI\n519: \n520: **Decision:** Distributed resolution (per spec) is more flexible.\n521: \n522: ## Implementation Checklist\n523: \n524: - [ ] Implement `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with validators\n525: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService` with load/save/update/validate\n526: - [ ] Create `MetadataOptions` dataclass with `from_options()`\n527: - [ ] Update `PackRuntime` to use `MetadataService`\n528: - [ ] Export `StatusRuntime` in `agentcube/__init__.py`\n529: - [ ] Write unit tests for metadata validation\n530: - [ ] Write integration tests for workspace validation\n531: - [ ] Update documentation to reflect `agent_metadata.yaml` naming\n532: - [ ] Add example `agent_metadata.yaml` to examples/\n533: \n534: ## Testing Strategy\n535: \n536: ### Unit Tests\n537: \n538: ```python\n539: # tests/test_metadata_service.py\n540: \n541: class TestAgentMetadata:\n542:     def test_valid_metadata(self):\n543:         metadata = AgentMetadata(\n544:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n545:             entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n546:             language=\"python\",\n547:             port=8080,\n548:         )\n549:         assert metadata.language == \"python\"\n550:         assert metadata.port == 8080\n551:     \n552:     def test_invalid_language(self):\n553:         with pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n554:             AgentMetadata(\n555:                 agent_name=\"test\",\n556:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n557:                 language=\"golang\",\n558:             )\n559:     \n560:     def test_invalid_port(self):\n561:         with pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n562:             AgentMetadata(\n563:                 agent_name=\"test\",\n564:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n565:                 port=70000,\n566:             )\n567: \n568: \n569: class TestMetadataService:\n570:     def test_load_metadata_primary(self, tmp_path):\n571:         metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n572:         metadata_file.write_text(\"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\")\n573:         \n574:         service = MetadataService()\n575:         metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n576:         \n577:         assert metadata.agent_name == \"test\"\n578:     \n579:     def test_load_metadata_fallback(self, tmp_path):\n580:         # Only agent.yaml exists\n581:         metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent.yaml\"\n582:         metadata_file.write_text(\"agent_name: fallback-test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\")\n583:         \n584:         service = MetadataService()\n585:         metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n586:         \n587:         assert metadata.agent_name == \"fallback-test\"\n588:     \n589:     def test_validate_python_workspace_no_files(self, tmp_path):\n590:         service = MetadataService()\n591:         \n592:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"No Python files found\"):\n593:             service.validate_workspace(tmp_path)\n594:     \n595:     def test_validate_java_workspace_no_pom(self, tmp_path):\n596:         # Create a Python file to satisfy language detection\n597:         (tmp_path / \"Main.java\").write_text(\"public class Main {}\")\n598:         \n599:         service = MetadataService()\n600:         # Manually set language to java\n601:         metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n602:         metadata_file.write_text(\n603:             \"agent_name: java-test\\nentrypoint: java Main\\nlanguage: java\"\n604:         )\n605:         \n606:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"pom.xml not found\"):\n607:             service.validate_workspace(tmp_path)\n608: ```\n609: \n610: ### Integration Tests\n611: \n612: ```python\n613: # tests/test_pack_runtime.py\n614: \n615: class TestPackRuntimeIntegration:\n616:     def test_full_pack_flow(self, tmp_path):\n617:         # Create workspace structure\n618:         (tmp_path / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\")\n619:         (tmp_path / \"requirements.txt\").write_text(\"requests\\n\")\n620:         \n621:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n622:         result = runtime.pack(tmp_path)\n623:         \n624:         assert \"agent_name\" in result\n625:         assert \"metadata_path\" in result\n626:         assert (tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").exists()\n627: ```\n628: \n629: ## Future Considerations\n630: \n631: 1. **Metadata versioning** - Schema version field for migration support\n632: 2. **Secret management** - Integrate with Kubernetes secrets or external vaults\n633: 3. **Metadata templates** - Pre-configured templates for common agent types\n634: 4. **Validation plugins** - Extensible validation for custom languages\n635: 5. **Metadata diff/patch** - Track changes across packaging operations\n636: 6. **Workspace scaffolding** - `agentcube init` command to create workspace structure\n637: \n638: ## References\n639: \n640: - CLI Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n641: - CLI Specification: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n642: - Python SDK Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n643: - Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n644: - Pydantic Docs: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n645: - YAML Spec: https://yaml.org/spec/\n646: \n647: ## Acceptance Criteria\n648: \n649: | Criterion | Verification |\n650: |-----------|--------------|\n651: | `AgentMetadata` validates language | Pydantic rejects non-python/java |\n652: | `AgentMetadata` validates port | Rejects ports outside 1-65535 |\n653: | `MetadataService` loads primary file | Finds `agent_metadata.yaml` first |\n654: | `MetadataService` uses fallbacks | Loads `agent.yaml` if primary missing |\n655: | `MetadataService` saves correctly | Writes valid YAML with correct format |\n656: | Workspace validation works | Python requires .py, Java requires pom.xml |\n657: | `MetadataOptions.from_options()` maps | CLI dict converts to dataclass |\n658: | `StatusRuntime` exported | `from agentcube import StatusRuntime` works |\n659: \n660: ---\n661: \n662: **Document Version:** 1.0  \n663: **Last Updated:** 2026-04-11  \n664: **Author:** AgentCube Team  \n665: **Contact:** agentcube@volcano.sh  \n666: **AR:** AR-025  \n667: **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n\n(End of file - total 667 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `MetadataService` and associated data models for the AgentCube CLI toolkit (`cmd/cli`). The goal is to:\n\n1. **Centralize metadata management** - Provide a single source of truth for agent configuration across the CLI\n2. **Enable workspace validation** - Validate agent workspace structure and language-specific requirements\n3. **Support metadata lifecycle** - Load, save, update, and validate agent metadata throughout the agent lifecycle\n4. **Ensure schema correctness** - Use Pydantic validation to enforce metadata schema constraints\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871571399,"end":1775871571406}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871571481,"sessionID":"ses_285cee01cffe6FVMs7Bj8Kv4Ql","part":{"id":"prt_d7a31ae7b001qc78AhJcoPzUKH","messageID":"msg_d7a31a20f001iWWAK8y2UvsERd","sessionID":"ses_285cee01cffe6FVMs7Bj8Kv4Ql","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e5e4b27646124d049c2b1a0c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Tests for the metadata service.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: import pytest\n4: from pathlib import Path\n5: import tempfile\n6: import yaml\n7: \n8: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n9: \n10: \n11: class TestAgentMetadata:\n12:     \"\"\"Test cases for AgentMetadata.\"\"\"\n13: \n14:     def test_create_valid_metadata(self):\n15:         \"\"\"Test creating valid metadata.\"\"\"\n16:         metadata = AgentMetadata(\n17:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n18:             language=\"python\",\n19:             entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n20:             port=8080,\n21:             build_mode=\"local\",\n22:         )\n23: \n24:         assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n25:         assert metadata.language == \"python\"\n26:         assert metadata.port == 8080\n27:         assert metadata.build_mode == \"local\"\n28: \n29:     def test_language_validation(self):\n30:         \"\"\"Test language validation.\"\"\"\n31:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Language must be 'python' or 'java'\"):\n32:             AgentMetadata(\n33:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n34:                 language=\"invalid\",\n35:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n36:             )\n37: \n38:     def test_language_case_normalization(self):\n39:         \"\"\"Test language case normalization.\"\"\"\n40:         metadata = AgentMetadata(\n41:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n42:             language=\"PYTHON\",\n43:             entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n44:         )\n45: \n46:         assert metadata.language == \"python\"\n47: \n48:     def test_build_mode_validation(self):\n49:         \"\"\"Test build mode validation.\"\"\"\n50:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Build mode must be 'local' or 'cloud'\"):\n51:             AgentMetadata(\n52:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n53:                 language=\"python\",\n54:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n55:                 build_mode=\"invalid\",\n56:             )\n57: \n58:     def test_port_validation(self):\n59:         \"\"\"Test port validation.\"\"\"\n60:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Port must be between 1 and 65535\"):\n61:             AgentMetadata(\n62:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n63:                 language=\"python\",\n64:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n65:                 port=70000,\n66:             )\n67: \n68:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Port must be between 1 and 65535\"):\n69:             AgentMetadata(\n70:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n71:                 language=\"python\",\n72:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n73:                 port=0,\n74:             )\n75: \n76: \n77: class TestMetadataService:\n78:     \"\"\"Test cases for MetadataService.\"\"\"\n79: \n80:     def test_save_and_load_metadata(self):\n81:         \"\"\"Test saving and loading metadata.\"\"\"\n82:         with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n83:             workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n84: \n85:             metadata = AgentMetadata(\n86:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n87:                 language=\"python\",\n88:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n89:                 port=8080,\n90:                 build_mode=\"local\",\n91:             )\n92: \n93:             service = MetadataService()\n94:             service.save_metadata(workspace, metadata)\n95: \n96:             loaded_metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace)\n97: \n98:             assert loaded_metadata.agent_name == metadata.agent_name\n99:             assert loaded_metadata.language == metadata.language\n100:             assert loaded_metadata.port == metadata.port\n101: \n102:     def test_load_metadata_fallback(self):\n103:         \"\"\"Test loading metadata with fallback files.\"\"\"\n104:         with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n105:             workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n106: \n107:             metadata = AgentMetadata(\n108:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n109:                 language=\"python\",\n110:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n111:             )\n112: \n113:             service = MetadataService()\n114: \n115:             metadata_file = workspace / \"agent.yaml\"\n116:             with open(metadata_file, \"w\") as f:\n117:                 yaml.dump(metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True), f)\n118: \n119:             loaded_metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace)\n120:             assert loaded_metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n121: \n122:     def test_update_metadata(self):\n123:         \"\"\"Test updating metadata.\"\"\"\n124:         with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n125:             workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n126: \n127:             metadata = AgentMetadata(\n128:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n129:                 language=\"python\",\n130:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n131:                 port=8080,\n132:             )\n133: \n134:             service = MetadataService()\n135:             service.save_metadata(workspace, metadata)\n136: \n137:             updated_metadata = service.update_metadata(\n138:                 workspace, {\"port\": 9090, \"description\": \"Updated\"}\n139:             )\n140: \n141:             assert updated_metadata.port == 9090\n142:             assert updated_metadata.description == \"Updated\"\n143: \n144:     def test_validate_workspace_exists(self):\n145:         \"\"\"Test workspace validation when workspace exists.\"\"\"\n146:         with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n147:             workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n148:             service = MetadataService()\n149: \n150:             assert service.validate_workspace(workspace) is True\n151: \n152:     def test_validate_workspace_not_exists(self):\n153:         \"\"\"Test workspace validation when workspace doesn't exist.\"\"\"\n154:         workspace = Path(\"/nonexistent/path\")\n155:         service = MetadataService()\n156: \n157:         with pytest.raises(FileNotFoundError, match=\"does not exist\"):\n158:             service.validate_workspace(workspace)\n159: \n160:     def test_load_metadata_not_found(self):\n161:         \"\"\"Test loading metadata when file doesn't exist.\"\"\"\n162:         with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n163:             workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n164:             service = MetadataService()\n165: \n166:             with pytest.raises(FileNotFoundError, match=\"No metadata file found\"):\n167:                 service.load_metadata(workspace)\n168: \n169:     def test_save_excludes_none_values(self):\n170:         \"\"\"Test that save excludes None values.\"\"\"\n171:         with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n172:             workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n173: \n174:             metadata = AgentMetadata(\n175:                 agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n176:                 language=\"python\",\n177:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n178:                 port=8080,\n179:                 description=None,\n180:                 region=None,\n181:             )\n182: \n183:             service = MetadataService()\n184:             service.save_metadata(workspace, metadata)\n185: \n186:             metadata_file = workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n187:             with open(metadata_file) as f:\n188:                 data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n189: \n190:             assert \"description\" not in data\n191:             assert \"region\" not in data\n192:             assert \"agent_name\" in data\n\n(End of file - total 192 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Tests for the metadata service.\"\"\"\n\nimport pytest\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport tempfile\nimport yaml\n\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n\n\nclass TestAgentMetadata:\n    \"\"\"Test cases for AgentMetadata.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_create_valid_metadata(self):\n        \"\"\"Test creating valid metadata.\"\"\"\n        metadata = AgentMetadata(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            language=\"python\",\n            entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n            port=8080,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py","time":{"start":1775871571396,"end":1775871571456}}}}
