te valid Python workspace (with .py file)\n  - Call validate_workspace\n  - Assert returns True\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Verify: Valid workspace accepted\n\n- [ ] **T7.7** Implement `TestMetadataService.test_validate_python_workspace_no_files`\n  - Create workspace without .py files\n  - Call validate_workspace\n  - Expect `ValueError` with \"No Python files found\"\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Verify: Invalid workspace rejected\n\n- [ ] **T7.8** Implement `TestMetadataService.test_validate_java_workspace_no_pom`\n  - Create workspace with language=\"java\"\n  - No pom.xml present\n  - Call validate_workspace\n  - Expect `ValueError` with \"pom.xml not found\"\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Verify: Java workspace requires pom.xml\n\n- [ ] **T7.9** Implement `TestMetadataService.test_yaml_format_preserves_order`\n  - Save metadata with specific field order\n  - Read YAML and verify field order\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Verify: `sort_keys=False` preserves order\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: Unit Tests - MetadataOptions\n\n- [ ] **T8.1** Implement `TestMetadataOptions.test_default_values`\n  - Create MetadataOptions with no args\n  - Assert all defaults correct\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_models.py`\n  - Verify: Defaults match spec\n\n- [ ] **T8.2** Implement `TestMetadataOptions.test_from_options_mapping`\n  - Create dict with CLI-style options\n  - Call `from_options()`\n  - Assert all fields mapped correctly\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_models.py`\n  - Verify: Dict to dataclass conversion\n\n- [ ] **T8.3** Implement `TestMetadataOptions.test_from_options_with_defaults`\n  - Create dict with missing optional fields\n  - Call `from_options()`\n  - Assert defaults applied for missing fields\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_models.py`\n  - Verify: Graceful handling of partial options\n\n---\n\n## Phase 9: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **T9.1** Implement `TestPackRuntimeIntegration.test_full_pack_flow`\n  - Create workspace with main.py and requirements.txt\n  - Call `PackRuntime.pack()`\n  - Assert result contains agent_name, metadata_path\n  - Assert agent_metadata.yaml created\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: End-to-end pack workflow\n\n- [ ] **T9.2** Implement `TestPackRuntimeIntegration.test_pack_with_existing_metadata`\n  - Create workspace with existing agent_metadata.yaml\n  - Call `PackRuntime.pack()`\n  - Assert existing metadata loaded and preserved\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Existing metadata respected\n\n- [ ] **T9.3** Implement `TestPackRuntimeIntegration.test_pack_with_option_overrides`\n  - Create workspace with metadata\n  - Call pack() with port override\n  - Assert metadata updated with override\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: CLI options override metadata\n\n---\n\n## Phase 10: Code Quality\n\n- [ ] **T10.1** Run mypy type checking\n  - Command: `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n  - Fix all type errors\n  - Verify: No mypy errors\n\n- [ ] **T10.2** Run mypy on pack_models\n  - Command: `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n  - Fix all type errors\n  - Verify: No mypy errors\n\n- [ ] **T10.3** Run ruff linting\n  - Command: `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/`\n  - Fix all lint errors\n  - Verify: No ruff errors\n\n- [ ] **T10.4** Run pytest with coverage\n  - Command: `pytest --cov=agentcube.services.metadata_service cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Verify coverage >= 80%\n  - Verify: All methods tested\n\n- [ ] **T10.5** Verify backward compatibility\n  - Test loading old agent.yaml files\n  - Test loading old metadata.yaml files\n  - Verify: Fallback mechanism works\n\n---\n\n## Phase 11: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **T11.1** Add comprehensive docstrings to `AgentMetadata`\n  - Document all field groups\n  - Include example usage\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n  - Verify: `help(AgentMetadata)` displays correctly\n\n- [ ] **T11.2** Add comprehensive docstrings to `MetadataService` methods\n  - Document parameters with types\n  - Document return values\n  - Document all exceptions\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n  - Verify: Complete API documentation\n\n- [ ] **T11.3** Add docstrings to `MetadataOptions`\n  - Document purpose\n  - Document `from_options()` usage\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n  - Verify: Clear documentation\n\n- [ ] **T11.4** Create example `agent_metadata.yaml`\n  - Show all fields with realistic values\n  - Include comments explaining sections\n  - File: `examples/agent_metadata.yaml`\n  - Verify: Example is valid YAML\n\n- [ ] **T11.5** Update README with MetadataService usage\n  - Show instantiation\n  - Show load/save/update examples\n  - Show workspace validation\n  - File: `cmd/cli/README.md` or docstrings\n  - Verify: Examples are runnable\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `AgentMetadata` model implements all 22 fields with correct types\n2. ✅ `validate_language` rejects non-python/java values\n3. ✅ `validate_build_mode` rejects non-local/cloud values\n4. ✅ `validate_port` rejects ports outside 1-65535\n5. ✅ `MetadataService.load_metadata()` tries fallbacks in order\n6. ✅ `MetadataService.save_metadata()` excludes None values\n7. ✅ `MetadataService.update_metadata()` performs partial updates\n8. ✅ `MetadataService.validate_workspace()` checks Python/Java requirements\n9. ✅ `MetadataOptions.from_options()` maps CLI dict correctly\n10. ✅ `PackRuntime` integrates with `MetadataService`\n11. ✅ `StatusRuntime` exported in `agentcube.__all__`\n12. ✅ Unit tests cover all validators and methods (>= 80% coverage)\n13. ✅ Integration tests verify full pack workflow\n14. ✅ Docstrings follow Google/NumPy style conventions\n15. ✅ Type hints pass mypy validation\n16. ✅ Example `agent_metadata.yaml` provided\n\n---\n\n**Notes:**\n- S